What you need to know:

By Saturday evening, one out of the record field of 158 golfers drawn from Kenya Railway Golf Club, Golf Park, Royal Nairobi, Kenya Airforce, Ruiru, Mombasa Golf Club and hosts Machakos, will have been declared the ICEA Lion King of the Course 2021 Machakos editionThe 2020 Machakos leg was held on January 4, where home player James Ndunda then playing off handicap six carded 37 points in an event played on a tough course then, to become the 2020 King of The CourseBecause of the big entry, 82 players are drawn in the morning from 6am while 76 players will be battling it out in the afternoon